WEBVTT


00:00:11.813 --> 00:00:16.938
Ms. Yakushimae has agreed
to support you as your guarantor again.

00:00:19.188 --> 00:00:23.355
You'll stay at a shelter for a while,
so your whereabouts won't be discovered.

00:00:23.438 --> 00:00:25.188
We'll also help you secure a job.

00:00:25.730 --> 00:00:28.938
So let's completely cut ties
with Suguru Kanemoto.

00:00:29.021 --> 00:00:30.438
You can start a new life.

00:00:35.605 --> 00:00:37.105
The same thing will happen.

00:00:38.063 --> 00:00:40.480
No matter how far I go,
nothing will change.

00:00:40.980 --> 00:00:41.813
Yeah.

00:00:43.105 --> 00:00:46.896
I'll just fall into
the same rotten swamp again.

00:00:48.855 --> 00:00:50.230
POOP

00:00:50.313 --> 00:00:51.896
It's just my fate.

00:00:53.938 --> 00:00:56.271
The other day, I met with your father.

00:00:56.855 --> 00:00:57.771
What?

00:00:58.813 --> 00:01:02.063
Sota got arrested again?

00:01:02.646 --> 00:01:06.646
If he cuts ties with Mr. Kanemoto,
his situation might change for the better.

00:01:06.730 --> 00:01:08.480
Please lend us your strength.

00:01:08.563 --> 00:01:15.438
I'm in no position
to say anything to Sota at this point.

00:01:15.521 --> 00:01:16.730
I'm sorry.

00:01:19.355 --> 00:01:21.355
Why don't you get your tattoo removed?

00:01:22.938 --> 00:01:26.730
The tattoo on your forehead.
Mr. Kanemoto's father did that, didn't he?

00:01:27.313 --> 00:01:29.396
Sota has the same tattoo on his arm.

00:01:29.980 --> 00:01:32.563
If you get it removed,
it might change how he feels.

00:01:33.188 --> 00:01:35.396
Let's get it removed for Sota's sake.

00:01:40.605 --> 00:01:42.688
Would that help Sota?

00:01:43.771 --> 00:01:45.313
Yes, it will help him.

00:01:49.188 --> 00:01:50.896
Then I'll get it removed.

00:01:52.855 --> 00:01:56.813
I'll do anything if it'll help Sota.

00:01:57.855 --> 00:01:59.230
For me?

00:02:00.063 --> 00:02:02.355
Yes. That's what he said.

00:02:03.896 --> 00:02:06.855
The doctor told your dad,

00:02:06.938 --> 00:02:09.813
"It's going to hurt.
Are you sure you want to do it?"

00:02:11.396 --> 00:02:13.355
But he insisted on having it removed.

00:02:15.396 --> 00:02:17.730
He said you got into prison

00:02:18.230 --> 00:02:20.730
because he was pathetic.

00:02:21.480 --> 00:02:24.188
He said he's been blaming himself
all this time.

00:02:25.730 --> 00:02:27.021
Mr. Sogabe,

00:02:27.855 --> 00:02:29.730
let's testify truthfully.

00:02:43.521 --> 00:02:45.438
Nah, I'm sorry. I still can't do it.

00:02:45.521 --> 00:02:49.105
What? Sota Sogabe! Why not?

00:02:49.188 --> 00:02:52.438
Given how this conversation's going,
you're supposed to say "yes."

00:02:52.521 --> 00:02:54.855
It's stupid to take the blame
for someone else!

00:02:54.938 --> 00:02:57.313
No, you two don't understand anything.

00:02:59.021 --> 00:03:01.355
I need to take the blame.

00:03:02.021 --> 00:03:02.855
Huh?

00:03:02.938 --> 00:03:04.230
What do you mean?

00:03:05.230 --> 00:03:08.271
Attorney Kujo came to visit me yesterday.

00:03:08.938 --> 00:03:12.688
Because of the marijuana and cocaine
that they found in your home,

00:03:12.771 --> 00:03:15.605
the police arrested Mr. Kanemoto
as an accomplice.

00:03:17.021 --> 00:03:17.855
Yes.

00:03:17.938 --> 00:03:21.855
The police want you to get three years
in prison for possession for profit.

00:03:22.396 --> 00:03:27.230
But if you insist that it was
simple possession for personal use,

00:03:27.313 --> 00:03:29.896
you'll only get
a year and a half in prison.

00:03:34.605 --> 00:03:36.146
That's why

00:03:36.646 --> 00:03:39.355
you need to take all the blame.

00:03:41.355 --> 00:03:43.521
You must never fess up about Mr. Kanemoto.

00:03:44.730 --> 00:03:46.230
I know.

00:03:46.730 --> 00:03:48.938
I'm fine with staying like this forever.

00:03:50.646 --> 00:03:51.980
No, that's wrong.

00:03:53.480 --> 00:03:55.813
The law protects people's rights,

00:03:55.896 --> 00:03:59.063
but it can't protect people's lives.

00:04:00.271 --> 00:04:03.021
If you fess up now about Mr. Kanemoto,

00:04:03.105 --> 00:04:04.855
you'll be killed when you get out.

00:04:06.230 --> 00:04:09.021
If you and Mr. Kanemoto were to cut ties,

00:04:09.105 --> 00:04:11.063
it'd only be after you serve your time.

00:04:11.980 --> 00:04:14.271
I can't guarantee your safety otherwise.

00:04:15.938 --> 00:04:21.480
Attorney Kujo is protecting my life.

00:05:04.438 --> 00:05:05.313
Huh?

00:05:09.521 --> 00:05:10.688
Oh, there he is.

00:05:13.021 --> 00:05:14.521
Attorney Kujo.

00:05:14.605 --> 00:05:16.021
Attorney Karasuma.

00:05:17.230 --> 00:05:20.271
Just as I expected,
the sauce stain won't come out.

00:05:20.355 --> 00:05:21.188
Huh?

00:05:22.021 --> 00:05:22.855
Well,

00:05:22.938 --> 00:05:26.438
I really wanted to eat the takoyaki
from "Japan's top takoyaki,"

00:05:26.521 --> 00:05:28.271
but the shop was closed.

00:05:28.355 --> 00:05:32.521
So I had no choice but to eat takoyaki
from another place. Then this happened.

00:05:32.605 --> 00:05:36.146
Attorney Kujo,
Mr. Sogabe was grateful to you.

00:05:36.230 --> 00:05:38.313
He said you protected his life.

00:05:42.771 --> 00:05:44.355
Thank you.

00:05:45.605 --> 00:05:47.855
I don't judge my clients
based on their status

00:05:47.938 --> 00:05:49.855
or whether they're good or bad.

00:05:49.938 --> 00:05:53.980
As an attorney,
I was simply on my client's side.

00:05:56.021 --> 00:05:57.188
But

00:05:57.855 --> 00:06:00.146
even though I can help them with the law,

00:06:00.230 --> 00:06:01.896
I can't look after their lives.

00:06:02.855 --> 00:06:04.396
Look after their lives?

00:06:05.480 --> 00:06:09.313
Even after the trial is over,
his life will keep going,

00:06:09.396 --> 00:06:12.730
and it's not an attorney
who can help with that.

00:06:13.605 --> 00:06:16.938
It's the people who care about him
and are always by his side.

00:06:59.730 --> 00:07:01.271
I'm home.

00:07:06.188 --> 00:07:07.563
Shinji?

00:07:07.646 --> 00:07:09.813
Mom, the flowers
in the garden are withered.

00:07:09.896 --> 00:07:12.021
What happened? You took good care of them.

00:07:12.105 --> 00:07:14.438
Never mind that. What's going on with you?

00:07:14.521 --> 00:07:16.355
I came to get my summer clothes.

00:07:16.438 --> 00:07:17.938
Oh, I see.

00:07:18.730 --> 00:07:21.355
Mom, the weather is so nice now.

00:07:24.146 --> 00:07:26.230
Why don't you go outside once in a while?

00:07:26.313 --> 00:07:28.813
You used to like things
like musicals and concerts.

00:07:28.896 --> 00:07:30.271
It's okay.

00:07:30.355 --> 00:07:34.230
If someone saw me having fun outside,
who knows what they would say.

00:07:34.313 --> 00:07:36.230
How long will you keep saying that?

00:07:36.313 --> 00:07:38.980
It's already been 18 years
since Dad passed away.

00:07:43.355 --> 00:07:45.980
Oh, Mom. This is the one Dad liked.

00:07:46.063 --> 00:07:47.355
Eat it later.

00:08:33.688 --> 00:08:36.688
ESSENTIAL GUIDE TO THE SIX CODES
FOR BEGINNERS

00:08:40.188 --> 00:08:42.396
THE SIGNIFICANCE OF STUDYING LAW

00:08:48.646 --> 00:08:50.896
Thank you, Attorney Kujo.

00:08:51.480 --> 00:08:54.480
To think, Kanemoto
was actually cut loose in 20 days.

00:08:54.563 --> 00:08:57.105
What's important
is not getting prosecuted.

00:08:57.188 --> 00:09:00.021
Time is precious for everyone.

00:09:01.105 --> 00:09:02.771
There's no value in winning

00:09:02.855 --> 00:09:04.355
a not-guilty verdict in court.

00:09:06.563 --> 00:09:08.021
This case has made you

00:09:08.105 --> 00:09:10.646
a hot topic among us.

00:09:11.521 --> 00:09:14.396
Attorney Kujo, I'm really grateful.

00:09:14.896 --> 00:09:19.438
I want to express how I feel right now
to everyone in the world through rap.

00:09:20.105 --> 00:09:21.271
Attorney Kujo.

00:09:21.355 --> 00:09:23.563
Thank you. You're the best.

00:09:23.646 --> 00:09:27.105
I was really cut loose in 20 days.
It's unbelievable.

00:09:27.188 --> 00:09:30.313
You ratted me out, and I got locked up.

00:09:30.396 --> 00:09:33.438
You got your head hammered in.

00:09:35.646 --> 00:09:41.105
Would you like to join us for Japanese BBQ
to celebrate Kanemoto's release?

00:09:41.771 --> 00:09:44.313
I can't because work is piling up.

00:09:44.896 --> 00:09:46.896
I see. Understood.

00:09:50.021 --> 00:09:53.563
I'll be needing your services again soon.

00:09:58.563 --> 00:09:59.396
Huh?

00:10:02.896 --> 00:10:03.813
Huh?

00:10:03.896 --> 00:10:04.938
I…

00:10:05.021 --> 00:10:07.396
I'm taking the blame?

00:10:16.146 --> 00:10:18.480
So Mr. Kanemoto has been set free?

00:10:20.438 --> 00:10:24.313
I imagine he'll now put more effort
into perfecting his awful rapping skills.

00:10:24.396 --> 00:10:26.938
He'll get close to Mr. Sogabe
when he gets out.

00:10:28.021 --> 00:10:29.271
I'd imagine so.

00:10:37.771 --> 00:10:39.313
I'm going out for a bit.

00:10:46.563 --> 00:10:47.980
I see.

00:10:49.355 --> 00:10:53.771
So Kanemoto's son… has been released.

00:10:55.355 --> 00:10:59.271
I'm sure that Sota won't be able
to cut ties with him on his own.

00:11:00.021 --> 00:11:02.146
He won't be able to escape this situation.

00:11:03.021 --> 00:11:05.396
He'll need support after he gets out too.

00:11:05.480 --> 00:11:07.230
Support from his parents.

00:11:08.438 --> 00:11:10.355
I understand what you're saying.

00:11:10.855 --> 00:11:13.355
I'll talk to Sota and say,

00:11:13.438 --> 00:11:16.230
"When you get out of prison,
let's live together."

00:11:27.938 --> 00:11:29.605
This urn holds my wife's ashes.

00:11:31.480 --> 00:11:36.438
When Sota was about to graduate
from elementary school,

00:11:36.938 --> 00:11:38.646
my wife left us.

00:11:38.730 --> 00:11:40.146
For years,

00:11:41.313 --> 00:11:43.396
I couldn't reach her.

00:11:44.063 --> 00:11:45.521
But three years ago,

00:11:46.646 --> 00:11:49.521
she came back to me as ashes.

00:11:50.438 --> 00:11:51.855
Is that so?

00:11:53.105 --> 00:11:55.813
I don't think Sota remembers her much.

00:11:55.896 --> 00:11:57.146
Oh, he remembers her.

00:12:00.355 --> 00:12:04.063
He told me about the time
his mother came to see him on field day.

00:12:05.521 --> 00:12:06.646
Field day?

00:12:11.771 --> 00:12:16.480
She was looking down, and she was looking
like it was the end of the world.

00:12:16.563 --> 00:12:20.063
I think she was embarrassed
and frustrated.

00:12:20.146 --> 00:12:22.438
Sota said his mom was embarrassed by him,

00:12:24.063 --> 00:12:26.730
and she was looking down.

00:12:28.355 --> 00:12:29.355
That's not true!

00:12:29.938 --> 00:12:30.771
That's…

00:12:31.855 --> 00:12:33.021
That's not true.

00:12:35.063 --> 00:12:35.896
COURTHOUSE

00:12:35.980 --> 00:12:37.021
The verdict…

00:12:37.521 --> 00:12:41.980
The defendant is sentenced
to one year and six months in prison.

00:12:42.480 --> 00:12:44.521
A sincere heart that says, "yes."

00:12:44.605 --> 00:12:47.480
A sincere heart that says, "yes."

00:12:47.563 --> 00:12:50.063
A repentant heart that says, "I'm sorry."

00:12:50.146 --> 00:12:52.563
A repentant heart that says, "I'm sorry."

00:12:52.646 --> 00:12:54.938
A humble heart that says,
"My thanks to you."

00:12:55.521 --> 00:12:58.355
A humble heart that says,
"My thanks to you."

00:12:58.438 --> 00:13:01.396
A servant heart that says,
"Allow me to do this."

00:13:01.480 --> 00:13:04.438
A servant heart that says,
"Allow me to do this."

00:13:06.105 --> 00:13:09.521
This prison is full of old guys.

00:13:12.730 --> 00:13:16.188
I wonder if this guy
is around my dad's age.

00:13:18.438 --> 00:13:19.271
Sogabe.

00:13:19.896 --> 00:13:21.105
Yes.

00:13:21.188 --> 00:13:22.438
You have a visitor.

00:13:23.230 --> 00:13:24.271
Yes.

00:13:41.146 --> 00:13:42.146
What is it?

00:13:43.605 --> 00:13:45.105
Your dad said,

00:13:45.605 --> 00:13:49.021
"When you get out of prison,
let's live together."

00:13:50.563 --> 00:13:51.813
My dad said that?

00:13:53.480 --> 00:13:56.938
And about what happened on field day…

00:13:57.855 --> 00:14:00.313
You told me you came in last place.

00:14:00.396 --> 00:14:05.855
You said your mom looked down
and had a face like the world had ended.

00:14:07.813 --> 00:14:09.230
That wasn't true.

00:14:10.605 --> 00:14:13.438
Your dad was also there
for the same field day.

00:14:15.313 --> 00:14:17.230
Your mom was looking down,

00:14:17.980 --> 00:14:20.355
not because she was embarrassed,

00:14:21.230 --> 00:14:23.355
but because she saw you
giving it your all,

00:14:24.730 --> 00:14:26.146
and that made her cry.

00:14:30.855 --> 00:14:31.980
Mom…

00:14:33.105 --> 00:14:34.646
Sota.

00:14:37.438 --> 00:14:38.646
You can do it!

00:14:41.521 --> 00:14:43.230
You can do it!

00:14:56.188 --> 00:14:57.521
Mom…

00:15:01.605 --> 00:15:04.105
We're investigating Kanemoto
undercover once again,

00:15:04.188 --> 00:15:06.063
with a focus on the for-profit angle.

00:15:06.771 --> 00:15:10.230
We know you took the fall
for all of Kanemoto's crimes.

00:15:10.730 --> 00:15:12.605
Are you sure you're okay with this?

00:15:18.271 --> 00:15:22.605
Though it was simple possession,
you're in prison for a year and a half.

00:15:22.688 --> 00:15:24.563
Don't you think that's unfair?

00:15:29.438 --> 00:15:32.438
You were using a phone app
to communicate with Kanemoto

00:15:32.521 --> 00:15:34.688
so the police
couldn't intercept it, right?

00:15:35.188 --> 00:15:38.230
We'll have a special agency
analyze your smartphone, okay?

00:15:42.688 --> 00:15:46.605
Hey, how do you feel about that, Sogabe?

00:15:47.105 --> 00:15:49.063
Say something already.

00:15:55.355 --> 00:15:57.188
Detective, I have a favor to ask.

00:15:59.688 --> 00:16:00.688
What is it?

00:16:03.688 --> 00:16:06.105
POOP
STINKY

00:16:07.188 --> 00:16:08.896
I want to erase this.

00:16:16.271 --> 00:16:18.563
I want to erase this tattoo.

00:16:23.438 --> 00:16:24.438
Yes.

00:16:25.146 --> 00:16:30.146
CONGRATULATIONS
ON OPENING GIRLS BAR MILKEE

00:16:30.230 --> 00:16:33.438
I understand, Mr. Kyogoku.

00:16:50.188 --> 00:16:51.313
Mibu,

00:16:51.396 --> 00:16:55.605
congratulations on
the pre-opening of your girls bar.

00:16:55.688 --> 00:16:56.938
Sure.

00:16:57.021 --> 00:16:58.313
Mibu,

00:16:58.396 --> 00:17:01.813
you're doing well, even though
the nightlife business is tough now.

00:17:01.896 --> 00:17:03.730
Are you sure it's okay to invite me?

00:17:04.313 --> 00:17:05.438
Of course.

00:17:07.438 --> 00:17:08.605
The business card.

00:17:08.688 --> 00:17:09.896
Thanks.

00:17:11.730 --> 00:17:14.521
"Girls bar Milkee!"

00:17:17.396 --> 00:17:19.271
Are you not coming?

00:17:19.855 --> 00:17:22.980
There's a car I need to paint
and deliver by tomorrow.

00:17:24.063 --> 00:17:25.896
Hey, could you close the shutter?

00:17:26.688 --> 00:17:27.938
That orange button.

00:17:28.021 --> 00:17:29.146
Oh, okay.

00:17:33.563 --> 00:17:36.230
You're such a hard worker, Mibu.

00:17:37.396 --> 00:17:40.521
Do you always draw water
from the river and use it?

00:17:40.605 --> 00:17:43.105
Yeah. It saves money.

00:17:45.021 --> 00:17:46.355
Milkee.

00:17:47.688 --> 00:17:51.771
Miyoko, I'm sorry. I love you.

00:18:45.480 --> 00:18:46.730
Mibu.

00:18:48.188 --> 00:18:49.021
Mibu!

00:18:50.563 --> 00:18:51.396
Mibu!

00:19:06.605 --> 00:19:10.396
An executive of Fushimi-gumi
was busted for smuggling cocaine.

00:19:10.480 --> 00:19:14.021
That's the drug syndicate
Kanemoto and his men were dealing with.

00:19:14.105 --> 00:19:16.688
Could Kanemoto be the one
who snitched on them?

00:19:16.771 --> 00:19:17.980
No.

00:19:18.063 --> 00:19:21.271
Kanemoto has nothing to gain
by selling out Fushimi-gumi.

00:19:21.355 --> 00:19:23.480
There was another snitch.

00:19:23.563 --> 00:19:24.563
Who was it?

00:19:27.355 --> 00:19:28.813
It was Sota Sogabe.

00:19:29.605 --> 00:19:31.063
Mr. Sogabe?

00:19:32.021 --> 00:19:36.730
He took a shot at them
from inside the prison, where it was safe.

00:19:36.813 --> 00:19:38.480
Sogabe understands reason and logic,

00:19:38.563 --> 00:19:42.730
so he framed Kanemoto as the snitch
and took him out.

00:19:44.188 --> 00:19:46.646
He told the detective
who came to question him…

00:19:48.480 --> 00:19:52.313
"I want to erase my tattoo,
just like my father."

00:19:55.146 --> 00:19:58.855
He must have resolved
to finally break the vicious cycle.

00:20:03.813 --> 00:20:05.271
Attorney Karasuma,

00:20:06.105 --> 00:20:08.813
you actually managed to save him.

00:20:08.896 --> 00:20:09.896
You saved him.

00:20:17.813 --> 00:20:19.521
What's that look on your face?

00:20:21.063 --> 00:20:22.521
I'm happy, but…

00:20:23.813 --> 00:20:27.563
I don't know if I should say that.
My emotions haven't caught up yet.

00:20:28.938 --> 00:20:30.188
I see.

00:20:31.896 --> 00:20:36.146
Do you always live with these emotions,
Attorney Kujo?

00:20:37.355 --> 00:20:40.438
I've never really paid attention to them.

00:20:41.396 --> 00:20:42.730
I see.

00:20:46.521 --> 00:20:50.896
Anyway, what's important for Mr. Sogabe
is what happens from here.

00:20:51.855 --> 00:20:53.271
From here?

00:20:53.355 --> 00:20:55.188
It depends on Kanemoto's next move.

00:20:59.563 --> 00:21:02.480
He was found drowned.

00:21:02.563 --> 00:21:03.771
What?

00:21:12.230 --> 00:21:15.688
Cause of death was asphyxiation
from drinking a large amount of water.

00:21:15.771 --> 00:21:20.105
The water in his lungs matched
the water in this river mouth.

00:21:21.730 --> 00:21:24.688
So Kanemoto was killed to silence him?

00:22:00.813 --> 00:22:02.396
Oh, come in.

00:22:03.396 --> 00:22:05.688
Attorney Kujo,
Mr. Sogabe's father is here.

00:22:08.313 --> 00:22:09.313
Hello, there.

00:22:09.396 --> 00:22:14.646
Thank you for saving my son, sir.

00:22:16.313 --> 00:22:18.563
Your forehead is looking much cleaner.

00:22:18.646 --> 00:22:21.105
Oh, well…

00:22:21.188 --> 00:22:24.938
And you're letting me pay
the attorney's fees in installments,

00:22:25.021 --> 00:22:26.396
without interest.

00:22:26.480 --> 00:22:27.605
That's a great help.

00:22:27.688 --> 00:22:29.438
No problem. Thank you for coming.

00:22:29.521 --> 00:22:30.605
Of course.

00:22:30.688 --> 00:22:34.813
Please have this with everyone.

00:22:35.730 --> 00:22:38.313
Oh, thank you for your kindness.

00:22:40.230 --> 00:22:41.105
Oden?

00:22:41.188 --> 00:22:42.313
But it's summer.

00:22:42.396 --> 00:22:44.188
I went to four convenience stores

00:22:44.271 --> 00:22:48.605
and managed to buy only eggs, 25 of them!

00:22:48.688 --> 00:22:50.480
What a way to shop for oden.

00:22:50.563 --> 00:22:53.730
Sota and I love eggs.

00:22:53.813 --> 00:22:56.188
I hope you guys like them too.

00:22:59.146 --> 00:23:01.271
I prefer it with daikon.

00:23:02.396 --> 00:23:03.230
What?

00:23:03.313 --> 00:23:05.271
Did you have to say that?

00:23:06.813 --> 00:23:09.980
-Well, then, Ms. Yakushimae.
-I prefer it with fish cakes.

00:23:11.105 --> 00:23:13.146
Then I'll enjoy it.

00:23:14.146 --> 00:23:15.063
Go ahead.

00:23:15.146 --> 00:23:17.105
Thank you for the food.

00:23:17.730 --> 00:23:19.063
Wow, it looks so good.

00:23:21.771 --> 00:23:23.771
Mmm, it's good.

00:23:26.188 --> 00:23:27.646
By the way,

00:23:28.646 --> 00:23:33.355
the other day, Kanemoto's father
came to my house, and he was drunk.

00:23:50.105 --> 00:23:51.605
Sogabe.

00:23:53.188 --> 00:23:55.688
I'm sorry for everything.

00:23:57.021 --> 00:23:58.480
Please forgive me.

00:23:58.980 --> 00:24:00.646
To you,

00:24:01.563 --> 00:24:03.563
and to your son as well,

00:24:04.605 --> 00:24:07.146
I've done such terrible things.

00:24:09.313 --> 00:24:11.438
I regret it every day.

00:24:12.105 --> 00:24:14.063
So now you're crawling for forgiveness?

00:24:14.146 --> 00:24:17.146
I'll never forgive you!

00:24:17.813 --> 00:24:19.730
Go home!

00:24:38.188 --> 00:24:41.771
That Kanemoto, who'd been
so arrogantly overbearing,

00:24:43.063 --> 00:24:45.730
looked so small that day.

00:24:46.271 --> 00:24:48.980
I don't care about
what he's done to me until now.

00:24:49.938 --> 00:24:51.855
What he did to Sota is another matter.

00:24:53.646 --> 00:24:56.396
He must have felt lonely
after his son died.

00:24:57.480 --> 00:25:01.355
No matter what kind of son he was,
they were still family.

00:25:04.813 --> 00:25:06.771
Did you get to see Sota?

00:25:06.855 --> 00:25:09.271
Oh, yes, yes. I finally got to see him.

00:25:09.355 --> 00:25:10.396
Was he happy?

00:25:12.855 --> 00:25:16.605
We didn't know how
to act around each other,

00:25:16.688 --> 00:25:18.771
so we were silent for a good while.

00:25:21.188 --> 00:25:22.230
But

00:25:22.813 --> 00:25:25.563
we talked about living together

00:25:25.646 --> 00:25:28.855
when he completes his prison term
and gets out.

00:25:28.938 --> 00:25:30.688
Oh, that's good.

00:25:32.813 --> 00:25:36.480
Truly, thank you all so much.

00:25:50.938 --> 00:25:53.146
What's wrong, rookie?
Are you not gonna eat?

00:25:53.771 --> 00:25:55.730
Oh, yes… Just…

00:25:56.355 --> 00:26:01.188
He just witnessed the autopsy
of Kanemoto's drowned body.

00:26:01.271 --> 00:26:04.188
The pig's feet reminded me of the body.

00:26:05.605 --> 00:26:07.521
That's happened to me before.

00:26:08.105 --> 00:26:12.813
A perpetrator killed three employees at
a Chinese restaurant with a chef's knife.

00:26:12.896 --> 00:26:14.980
The restaurant was a sea of blood.

00:26:15.563 --> 00:26:19.146
Because of the smell and feel
of the scattered organs,

00:26:19.230 --> 00:26:21.730
I couldn't eat offal for a while.

00:26:23.813 --> 00:26:27.021
But once you get used to it,
it doesn't bother you at all.

00:26:28.938 --> 00:26:30.646
More importantly, Mr. Arashiyama,

00:26:31.396 --> 00:26:34.021
a member of Fushimi-gumi
killed Kanemoto, huh?

00:26:34.105 --> 00:26:35.188
No.

00:26:35.896 --> 00:26:38.146
He's not a member of that yakuza group,

00:26:38.230 --> 00:26:40.896
but the man named Mibu smells fishy.

00:26:42.605 --> 00:26:46.688
Mibu often got into trouble
with the police when he was a kid.

00:26:47.188 --> 00:26:49.396
But recently, he's gained some wisdom.

00:26:49.480 --> 00:26:53.896
Officially, he's the diligent manager
of an auto repair shop.

00:26:55.438 --> 00:26:58.813
But Mibu is connected to Fushimi-gumi
behind the scenes.

00:26:58.896 --> 00:27:02.355
He's making a lot of money in security
and the nightlife business.

00:27:02.438 --> 00:27:04.105
I've heard that too.

00:27:04.188 --> 00:27:07.896
He gets into trouble with gangs,
takes settlement money,

00:27:07.980 --> 00:27:09.230
and expands his power.

00:27:09.313 --> 00:27:13.063
We questioned him about the Kanemoto case,
but we got nothing.

00:27:13.563 --> 00:27:19.230
Also, I don't like the way
the attorney close to Mibu is acting.

00:27:19.313 --> 00:27:20.563
An attorney?

00:27:20.646 --> 00:27:21.980
Yeah.

00:27:22.063 --> 00:27:26.605
An attorney who hangs around delinquents
will soon screw up and lose his badge.

00:27:26.688 --> 00:27:27.646
No…

00:27:27.730 --> 00:27:32.855
That attorney, Kujo,
is quite competent and skilled.

00:27:34.438 --> 00:27:37.313
He'll be troublesome
to deal with eventually.

00:27:44.063 --> 00:27:45.438
Here. Here, come over here.

00:27:45.521 --> 00:27:49.396
-Hey. It's a treat. Here, here.
-Maybe it's afraid of you, Ms. Yakushimae.

00:27:49.480 --> 00:27:50.855
Huh? Why?

00:27:50.938 --> 00:27:52.688
Why would it be afraid of me?

00:27:52.771 --> 00:27:54.355
Here, I'm not scary. Come here.

00:27:54.438 --> 00:27:57.730
Then try giving this to Black Thunder.

00:27:57.813 --> 00:27:59.271
Black Thunder?

00:27:59.355 --> 00:28:01.730
-Huh?
-That's the dog's name.

00:28:02.771 --> 00:28:04.188
Do you want some?

00:28:05.730 --> 00:28:08.813
Hey, are you really going
to keep Kanemoto's dog?

00:28:08.896 --> 00:28:11.355
What drives your actions, Attorney Kujo?

00:28:11.438 --> 00:28:14.271
I tried to give the dog back
to Kanemoto's girlfriend,

00:28:14.355 --> 00:28:16.521
but she said she'd have it put down.

00:28:16.605 --> 00:28:18.188
Mibu asked me to keep it,

00:28:18.271 --> 00:28:22.105
because he said he couldn't move on
from his dog, Rice Cake, who passed away.

00:28:22.605 --> 00:28:24.563
So I had no choice.

00:28:25.230 --> 00:28:29.771
Rice Cake and Black Thunder…
Is it a trend to name dogs after food?

00:28:30.271 --> 00:28:31.646
I don't know.

00:28:32.605 --> 00:28:34.855
Well, I'm going out for a bit.

00:28:34.938 --> 00:28:35.855
Jogging?

00:28:37.730 --> 00:28:38.730
No.

00:28:39.938 --> 00:28:42.146
Today is my daughter's birthday.

00:28:42.230 --> 00:28:43.688
-Oh, Rino.
-Huh?

00:28:43.771 --> 00:28:44.938
How old is she now?

00:28:45.021 --> 00:28:46.521
She's five.

00:28:46.605 --> 00:28:47.646
She's that big, huh?

00:28:47.730 --> 00:28:49.521
Are you gonna celebrate with her?

00:28:50.813 --> 00:28:52.938
I'm not allowed to see her,

00:28:53.021 --> 00:28:56.063
so I sent her a present by mail.

00:28:57.313 --> 00:28:59.063
What? Then where are you going?

00:29:12.480 --> 00:29:14.230
Three, two, one.

00:29:14.313 --> 00:29:16.313
Jump!

00:29:16.396 --> 00:29:17.730
Ready…

00:29:17.813 --> 00:29:20.938
Three, two, one. Jump!

00:29:21.438 --> 00:29:23.813
Thank you for the present, Daddy.

00:29:28.188 --> 00:29:30.230
I feel bad for Attorney Kujo.

00:29:30.730 --> 00:29:33.230
He gave his ex-wife all his assets,

00:29:33.313 --> 00:29:36.896
and he's even paying child support,
but he still can't see his daughter.

00:29:38.230 --> 00:29:39.313
Oh, I see.

00:29:39.396 --> 00:29:41.605
That's why Attorney Kujo
is living in a tent.

00:29:42.105 --> 00:29:43.438
That's right.

00:29:45.396 --> 00:29:48.938
But usually, you'd file for mediation
for visitation rights.

00:29:49.021 --> 00:29:53.105
Well, I'm sure Attorney Kujo
has his own reasons,

00:29:53.188 --> 00:29:54.813
but I'm not sure what they are.

00:29:57.855 --> 00:30:00.605
If he didn't go to see his daughter,
then where'd he go?

00:30:01.355 --> 00:30:04.521
Hmm, probably… his father's place.

00:30:04.605 --> 00:30:06.563
Huh? Attorney Kujo's?

00:30:06.646 --> 00:30:08.230
You mean Prosecutor Kurama?

00:30:08.896 --> 00:30:10.021
Yeah.

00:30:10.105 --> 00:30:12.355
But he passed away a long time ago.

00:30:12.855 --> 00:30:13.938
Yeah.

00:30:14.855 --> 00:30:15.980
That's why.

00:30:23.396 --> 00:30:24.396
KURAMA FAMILY GRAVE

00:30:24.480 --> 00:30:28.938
His daughter's birthday
and his father's death anniversary

00:30:29.021 --> 00:30:31.063
are both on August 15th.

00:30:33.563 --> 00:30:34.730
Now, then.

00:30:35.605 --> 00:30:36.855
I think I'll head home.

00:30:38.646 --> 00:30:39.605
Oh, Ms. Yakushimae.

00:30:39.688 --> 00:30:40.688
Hmm?

00:30:40.771 --> 00:30:43.896
Why does Attorney Kujo use
his ex-wife's last name?

00:30:44.480 --> 00:30:46.771
You should ask him that yourself.

00:31:06.855 --> 00:31:08.313
What are you doing?

00:31:12.438 --> 00:31:17.271
What is a man disowned by his family
doing at the family grave?

00:31:19.396 --> 00:31:21.063
I'm praying to Mom.

00:31:21.563 --> 00:31:23.313
And to Dad, too, just in case.

00:31:24.313 --> 00:31:27.188
You are no longer a member
of the Kurama family,

00:31:28.188 --> 00:31:29.480
nor are you my brother.

00:31:31.021 --> 00:31:34.521
-There's no need to tell me that. I'll go.
-Take the flowers with you.

00:31:35.855 --> 00:31:37.480
They'll defile the grave.

00:31:42.563 --> 00:31:46.396
Your overbearing, commanding tone
is just like Dad's.

00:31:46.480 --> 00:31:50.521
I hear that you object to the ruling
of a trial that I presided over.

00:31:54.188 --> 00:31:55.521
It's true.

00:31:55.605 --> 00:31:58.146
Try telling me what your objection is.

00:32:00.855 --> 00:32:02.521
That defendant

00:32:03.271 --> 00:32:05.146
was insane.

00:32:05.730 --> 00:32:08.396
I don't think it's right
to seek the death penalty.

00:32:08.480 --> 00:32:12.438
That crazy murderer deserves
to be executed.

00:32:12.521 --> 00:32:15.563
Prosecutors have a duty
to respond to the victims' anguish

00:32:15.646 --> 00:32:17.605
and the public's desire for punishment.

00:32:17.688 --> 00:32:19.896
I'm saying that's being emotional.

00:32:20.396 --> 00:32:25.313
Although he was under the influence
of hallucinations and delusions,

00:32:25.396 --> 00:32:29.980
the evidence did not prove his actions
were fully controlled by his mental state.

00:32:30.980 --> 00:32:34.980
That's why the court chose
the death penalty.

00:32:35.063 --> 00:32:36.230
Is that wrong?

00:32:41.313 --> 00:32:42.396
Taiza.

00:32:42.896 --> 00:32:45.980
Do you seriously want
to become a prosecutor?

00:32:49.396 --> 00:32:53.605
Didn't you make a promise
to your late mother?

00:32:56.146 --> 00:32:58.730
It's because you're sloppy, Taiza.

00:32:58.813 --> 00:33:01.938
You're a half-assed dumbass
who failed the bar exam repeatedly.

00:33:02.021 --> 00:33:04.146
And now you've launched a law office?

00:33:05.146 --> 00:33:09.105
Guys like you only get pathetic cases
from pathetic clients, right?

00:33:10.313 --> 00:33:13.980
Even among us prosecutors,
bad rumors are spreading about you.

00:33:18.271 --> 00:33:22.230
You're a disgrace to the Kurama family.

00:33:26.646 --> 00:33:28.646
Even if you can't see it,

00:33:28.730 --> 00:33:30.480
there's something I can see.

00:33:32.230 --> 00:33:33.646
And what is that?

00:33:38.563 --> 00:33:41.313
Are you running away
because you can't convince me?

00:33:43.188 --> 00:33:46.021
You're a loser who always runs away.

00:34:00.105 --> 00:34:03.355
ATTORNEY YUZO YAMASHIRO

00:34:05.813 --> 00:34:08.063
Hello, this is Kujo.

00:34:09.146 --> 00:34:10.480
Wow.

00:34:11.855 --> 00:34:13.813
You really can drink.

00:34:13.896 --> 00:34:15.480
I'll make some more.

00:34:17.771 --> 00:34:19.813
No, sir. That's not allowed.

00:34:19.896 --> 00:34:21.813
Come on. Just a little bit.

00:34:21.896 --> 00:34:23.688
Right, Mr. Sugawara?

00:34:24.938 --> 00:34:26.271
Oh, jeez…

00:34:26.355 --> 00:34:29.521
Attorney Yamashiro,
your guest has arrived.

00:34:29.605 --> 00:34:30.813
Oh, he's arrived?

00:34:30.896 --> 00:34:32.855
It's been a while, Attorney Yamashiro.

00:34:33.438 --> 00:34:37.313
Attorney Kujo, what's with that outfit?
Are you in workout clothes?

00:34:37.396 --> 00:34:40.105
I was just out jogging.

00:34:41.146 --> 00:34:43.563
This is all pretty lavish for this hour.

00:34:43.646 --> 00:34:46.563
Well, I am a big spender here.

00:34:47.438 --> 00:34:50.313
Besides, today is the anniversary
of your father's death.

00:34:50.396 --> 00:34:51.480
Yes.

00:34:51.563 --> 00:34:53.230
Well, my respects to your father…

00:34:53.313 --> 00:34:55.438
Now, I want to introduce you to someone.

00:34:55.938 --> 00:34:58.271
This is Mr. Sugawara. He's a CEO.

00:34:59.563 --> 00:35:01.730
Hello, I'm Mr. Sugawara.

00:35:02.605 --> 00:35:04.188
I'm Attorney Kujo.

00:35:05.105 --> 00:35:06.063
Sir,

00:35:06.688 --> 00:35:08.813
I probably shouldn't say this,

00:35:08.896 --> 00:35:11.855
but he's the most competent attorney

00:35:11.938 --> 00:35:14.230
to ever go independent from our firm.

00:35:14.813 --> 00:35:17.230
He's like a son to me,
so you can trust him.

00:35:17.813 --> 00:35:19.021
You flatter me too much.

00:35:20.188 --> 00:35:22.396
Come on. Sit, sit. Let's have a drink.

00:35:22.980 --> 00:35:24.896
-Bring the best drink you have.
-Okay.

00:35:24.980 --> 00:35:26.938
Oh, I'll just have a regular highball.

00:35:27.021 --> 00:35:29.480
Don't be so stingy.

00:35:29.563 --> 00:35:33.563
You should get more clients
and make tons of money.

00:35:33.646 --> 00:35:35.438
You'll see a different world.

00:35:35.521 --> 00:35:38.438
Criminal defense is okay,
depending on how you approach it.

00:35:38.521 --> 00:35:40.480
You think so?

00:35:40.563 --> 00:35:44.730
All right. Today, I'll give you
the full lesson on how to make money.

00:35:44.813 --> 00:35:46.188
Okay?

00:35:46.271 --> 00:35:48.605
Yeah. Miss, when's it coming?

00:35:48.688 --> 00:35:51.146
You know that CEO, Mr. Sugawara…

00:35:51.230 --> 00:35:54.396
He says he's the CEO of a nursing home,

00:35:54.480 --> 00:35:56.938
but his main job is fraud and robbery.

00:35:58.105 --> 00:36:01.521
It's thugs like him
who have money these days.

00:36:02.646 --> 00:36:04.105
Well,

00:36:04.188 --> 00:36:07.271
he's far better than stingy lowlifes.

00:36:08.771 --> 00:36:12.605
Those stingy lowlifes
are just a menace to society.

00:36:14.146 --> 00:36:18.063
Just give them longer sentences,
and send them off to prison, one by one.

00:36:20.563 --> 00:36:22.813
Did you stop siding with your clients?

00:36:24.396 --> 00:36:25.313
Huh?

00:36:25.396 --> 00:36:26.980
You were the one who taught me

00:36:28.230 --> 00:36:31.230
that attorneys should always be
on the side of their clients.

00:36:38.771 --> 00:36:40.521
Attorney Kujo,

00:36:41.896 --> 00:36:43.855
what is an attorney?

00:36:48.813 --> 00:36:50.730
You can't answer that, can you?

00:36:54.230 --> 00:36:55.813
Attorney Kujo,

00:36:55.896 --> 00:37:00.938
I… really think of you as my son.

00:37:03.563 --> 00:37:05.063
Thank you very much.

00:37:29.313 --> 00:37:30.355
Please, come in.

00:37:31.021 --> 00:37:32.896
Attorney Kujo, our client is here.

00:37:37.563 --> 00:37:38.730
Sir.

00:37:39.230 --> 00:37:42.146
Sir! Our client is here.

00:37:43.021 --> 00:37:44.688
Hello, I'm Attorney Kujo.

00:37:44.771 --> 00:37:46.313
He smells like alcohol.

00:37:46.396 --> 00:37:48.063
Are you sure about this guy?

00:37:48.563 --> 00:37:50.396
I'd like for you to handle my case.

00:37:50.480 --> 00:37:51.355
No, no.

00:37:52.313 --> 00:37:53.480
Have a seat.

00:38:01.188 --> 00:38:02.188
What's your name?

00:38:03.813 --> 00:38:05.188
It's Ms. Iemori.

00:38:06.105 --> 00:38:07.605
Hanae Iemori.

00:38:07.688 --> 00:38:08.980
Ms. Iemori.

00:38:10.855 --> 00:38:12.563
What would you like to discuss?

00:38:13.646 --> 00:38:15.771
I want to recover my father's inheritance.

00:38:16.355 --> 00:38:17.563
Inheritance?

00:38:18.271 --> 00:38:20.146
We found a handwritten will

00:38:20.230 --> 00:38:24.563
that said he'd donate 400 million yen
to an incorporated association.

00:38:24.646 --> 00:38:26.730
But my father wouldn't write that.

00:38:27.813 --> 00:38:31.146
This might sound rude,
but were you living with your father?

00:38:31.230 --> 00:38:32.230
No, I wasn't.

00:38:32.313 --> 00:38:36.021
He had dementia
and was living in a nursing home.

00:38:36.105 --> 00:38:37.605
Dementia…

00:38:39.230 --> 00:38:41.896
Those guys took advantage of that

00:38:42.896 --> 00:38:44.855
and tricked my father.

00:38:46.105 --> 00:38:49.855
-Who do you mean by "those guys"?
-The nursing home CEO and his lawyer.

00:38:49.938 --> 00:38:50.855
ATTORNEY YAMASHIRO

00:38:53.355 --> 00:38:54.771
My father, Shigenori Iemori,

00:38:54.855 --> 00:38:59.063
wrote that he'd donate all his assets
to the legal entity Kikogi.

00:38:59.146 --> 00:39:03.063
A man named Mr. Sugawara,
who's the CEO of the nursing home,

00:39:03.146 --> 00:39:06.896
and his attorney, Yuzo Yamashiro,
forced my father to write it.

00:39:08.271 --> 00:39:11.063
Please, sir.

00:39:11.730 --> 00:39:16.230
Please recover my father's inheritance
from that crooked lawyer and the CEO.

00:39:20.563 --> 00:39:22.063
I'm sorry,

00:39:23.355 --> 00:39:25.230
but I must decline this case.

00:39:25.896 --> 00:39:27.105
Why?

00:39:28.313 --> 00:39:31.980
I've been struggling, having been
passed around from lawyer to lawyer.

00:39:32.480 --> 00:39:36.521
But Mibu told me that Attorney Kujo
never turns down a case,

00:39:36.605 --> 00:39:38.771
no matter how troublesome it is.

00:39:41.063 --> 00:39:42.313
This time, I can't do it.

00:39:42.396 --> 00:39:43.896
You!

00:39:44.480 --> 00:39:48.188
Are you okay with letting a lawyer
who abets crime roam free?

00:42:35.563 --> 00:42:38.021
Subtitle translation by: Miho Kunisawa